/* Settings-difference class list. For every key defined in default.cfg,
   compare its default value against the current $GLOBALS['caSettings']
   entry; if the user has flipped it from the shipped default, emit a
   `ca_<key>` class. Keys not present in default.cfg are skipped (so
   runtime-only keys like unRaidVersion / dynamixTheme / favourite don't
   leak in). Lets CSS / future JS branch on user-configured deviations
   without re-reading the cfg files. The list rides on a hidden div near
   the top of the page body — never displayed, queried via JS or scoped
   selectors. */
$caSettingsClasses = [];
